body:
@soltanmm: we have a list of roots in the grpc source tree that is suitable for publicly trusted certs:
https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/etc/roots.pem

So what I would be inclined to do is to ship this with the python package as opposed to depend on the roots installed (or not) on the different platforms. Once you have it shipped with the python package, you can do python magic to resolve the path and set the right env var. This is what nodejs did and it looks like it's working well for them. @murgatroid99 can you confirm?
